BAUCHI – Thousands of supporters of the Governor of Kogi State, Yahaya Bello on Saturday besieged major streets of Bauchi metropolis to mobilize support for his 2023 presidential ambition. Daily Independent reports the supporters who trooped out in mass, commenced their rally from the Multi-purpose indoor sports hall, from where they proceeded through Kobi street, Emir drive, Central Market, then to the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa tomb. The development caused temporal traffic for some hours but was abated after they arrived at the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa tomb. The supporters sang and danced as they marched, carried banners, posters and other items with different inscriptions, announcing the presidential aspiration of the Kogi State Governor expressing their readiness to support him. At the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa tomb, Chief of Staff to the Governor, Pharmacist Abdulkareem Asuku Moh’d Jamiu thanked the crowd for coming to demonstrate their support for the presidential aspiration of his Principal who he described as a very youthful politician who has excelled where many older politicians have failed in the country. “Yahaya Bello is a youth, he has the youths who are the majority in the country at heart, he has been supporting the youths and women and in sha Allah, as the next President of Nigeria, he will do more for the youths and women”. ” Yahaya Bello will make the best of Nigeria in 2023 and will continue with all the good programs and policies of the President Muhammadu Buhari led APC administration and will even improve on them,” he said He appealed to all the supporters across political parties who are yet to have their voters cards to do so immediately now that INEC is doing the continuous voters registration because according to him, that is the only weapon they need to vote for Yahaya Bello as presidential candidate of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). POLL He warned them against engaging in any political thuggery that will smear the good image and integrity of Yahaya Bello stressing that, their President come 2023 hates violence and thuggery, you should therefore abhor such acts The crowd then moved to the Palace of the Emir of Bauchi, Dr Rilwanu Suleiman Adamu where the Chief of Staff presented the message of Yahaya Bello on his 2023 presidential aspirations seeking the Emir’s royal blessings. He assured that Yahaya Bello’s presidency of Nigeria will accord traditional rulers their places of respect, dignity and fathers of all just as he is presently doing in Kogi state in the past 7 years of his administration.